HEADWORD: Breastwork
<hw>Breast"work`</hw> <pr>(br⟦ecr⟧st"w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A defensive work of moderate height,
hastily thrown up, of earth or other material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A railing on the quarter-deck and
forecastle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

